Tags: Protected

Update Account

POST /api/account/update

Tags: Protected

Updates a user account, including whether or not his or her wish list is private. The updated user account is the one belonging to the session cookie.

If there is no session cookie or the account does not exist returns a 401, else returns a 200

application/json

    "accountType": "aliquip dolor consequat exercitation",

        "day": 2,
        "month": 8,
        "year": 1939

    "email": "consequat enim mollit eiusmod cupidatat",
    "houseNumber": "et non",
    "name": "consectetur ipsum Duis culpa laborum",
    "password": "irure",
    "postalCode": "ut in eiusmod",
    "registerDate": {
        "day": 9,
        "month": 12,
        "year": 1942
    },
    "streetName": "esse elit tempor non est",
    "surname": "eiusmod do incididunt",
    "wishlistPublic": true
}

Delete Favorite item

DELETE /api/favorite/{product-id}

Tags: Protected

Using the session cookie, deletes an item from the favorites list if it exists. Returns an error 401 if there is no session cookie or it does not match any user. Returns 400 error if the item is not favorited
session header string
product-id path string
200 OK
400 Bad Request
401 Unauthorized
Add Favorite item

POST /api/favorite/{product-id}

Tags: Protected

Adds a favorite item to the account associated with the session cookie username. If no session cookie exists, return 401 error.

The item can only be added if the user has ordered the item before. If he or she did not, it returns a 400 error.
session header string
product-id path string

text/plain

201 Created
Example for text/plain
"success"
productId: integer
400 Bad Request
Example for text/plain
"user has not yet bought this item"
401 Unauthorized
Example for text/plain
"user is not logged in"

Create Order

POST /api/order

Tags: Protected

Creates an order for the session id account. If no session is present, or the account does not exist, returns a 401 error. If the products do not exist or the order is empty, return a 400 error. Else returns 200 code

application/json 

[
    {
        "amount": 72,
        "productId": 492
    },
    {
        "amount": 12,
        "productId": 965
    },
    {
        "amount": 57,
        "productId": 487
    },
    {
        "amount": 37,
        "productId": 10
    }
]
object
productId: integer , { x | 1 x 1000 }
amount: integer , { x | 1 x 100 }
session header string

text/plain

201 Created
Example for text/plain
"Success"
400 Bad Request
Example for text/plain
"Order is empty / products do not exist"
401 Unauthorized
Example for text/plain
"Not logged in / account information invalid"
Get Order by id

GET /api/order/{id}

Tags: Protected

API checks whether the username in the session cookie matches the username for the order. Returns the order and 200 if they match, else returns a 401 error code.
session header string
id path string

200 OK

Delete Wishlist item

DELETE /api/wishlist/{product-id}

Tags: Protected

Deletes product from user wish list associated with session id. If user not logged in returns 401, if item not in wish list returns 400. else returns 200
session header string
product-id path string
200 OK
400 Bad Request
401 Unauthorized
Add Wishlist item

POST /api/wishlist/{product-id}

Tags: Protected

Adds the item to the wish list of the user matching the session cookie. If no session cookie is present, a 401 error is returned.

If the item already is part of the wishlist, a 400 error is returned.

If a wish is created, return a 201 status code
session header string
product-id path string

text/plain

201 Created
Example for text/plain
"success"
400 Bad Request
Example for text/plain
"something went wrong"
401 Unauthorized
Example for text/plain
"user is not logged in"
